The EQE of the devices are measured at room temperature in ambient atmosphere using a monochromator equipped with a xenon arc lamp. The monochromatic light is chopped at a frequency of 30 Hz and focused onto the sample. The active area is defined using a circular aperture with a diameter of 0.5 mm. The photocurrent at each wavelength I(λ) is measured with a lock-in amplifier (Ametek 1256) at 0 V. The light power at each wavelength P(λ) is measured, through the same aperture, with a calibrated photodiode (Newport 918D) placed at the same position of the device. Then, the EQE(%) value at each wavelength is determined using the following equation:2EQE(%)=100hcI(λ)/qλP(λ)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
